Evaluation criteria and weightings:
Mandatory Criteria
Contractor Safety & Environment Management Pre-qualification (Category 1) - Pass/Fail
Mandatory Site Inspection - Pass/Fail
Contractor Certification - Pass/Fail

Non-Price Criteria
Weighting (70%)
1. Capability and Experience - 20%
2. Proposed Delivery Methodology & Project Risk - 20%
3. Proposed Program of Work - 10%
4. Resourcing of Project Management Team & Depth of Alternative Resources for Key Positions - 10%
5. Quality Assurance, Environmental Management, Health & Safety Management - 10%

Price Criteria
Weighting (30%)
1. Lump Sum Price - 30%

TOTAL - 100%
Deliverables: Renew the protective coating on the Indooroopilly (Mains) Bridge
Contract milestones:
1. Re-paint the bridge superstructure steel truss spans, including internal and external surface. The Contractor is to ensure all grills are reinstated at the completion of Work inside the boxes each day. Where grills are missing, Queensland Rail will provide a grill/s for installation by the Contractor.
2. Replace defective rivets with huck bolts and defective steel members with new galvanised steel members
Optional Items to be approved by Queensland Rail:
3. Design and construct temporary transom deck. The temporary transom deck is required for Transom Replacement and re-railing works on both up and down mains. The transom replacement and re-railing works shall be undertaken by Queensland Rail. Once Queensland Rail has completed the transom replacement & re-railing works, the Contractor shall remove the temporary transom deck and associated items such as scaffolding. The design load criteria for the transom deck is five (5) kpa.
4. Provision and Installation of permanent gantry rails to underside of the bridge to support planned asset renewal work for each span (for a total of two (2) gantry rail. The design load criteria for gantry is four (4) kpa).
Contract performance management:
The Contractor is to appoint a Coating Supervisor holding a current coating inspection certificate.
The Contractor is to nominate the Coating Supervisor to the Superintendent prior to commencement of Work.
All Work may be subject to partial or full inspection by the Superintendent or his Representative. The Contractor is not relieved of his own Quality Assurance/Quality Control and coating system performance responsibilities.
Submit daily quality assurance records to the Superintendent for review and approval including:
a) Inspect and confirm that the substrate is fit to receive the nominated coatings in order to produce the specified finish and life expectancy.
b) Records confirming compliance with the Manufacturers recommendations and standards that specify minimum qualities of substrate preparation and coating application tolerances.
The Contractor shall notify the Superintendent in writing of an unfit substrate immediately after the problem is detected.
Direct inadequacies in the detailing of steelwork finishing or fabrication issues to the Superintendent.
